# Forestack monorepo layout

Open the workspace at the **repo root** (`INTERNAL-APP-TANSTACK/`), not the parent `INTERNAL-APP-STUFF/` folder. The parent folder does not contain `apps/` at its top level.

## Deployable apps

| App | Path | SaaS `/app` routes (studio) |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Studio (SaaS portal) | `apps/studio/` | `apps/studio/src/routes/_authed/app/` |
| Workspace (tenant portal) | `apps/workspace/` | `apps/workspace/src/routes/$companySlug/` |

Shared UI and Supabase clients: `packages/shared/`.

## Supabase

- CLI config: `supabase/config.toml`
- Edge Functions source: `supabase/functions/` (see `supabase/functions/README.md`)
- Project ref: `ocisdaeugliixyhcjnkv` (INTERNAL-APPLICATION)

## Git

If the explorer or SCM view looks empty, check that this folder is the workspace root and consider an initial commit so files are tracked (`git status` shows untracked until then).
